  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study hypothesis is that different concentrations of nucleotides' supplementation of an
      infant formula might affect differently growth and/or other clinical parameters in neonates.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Three groups of 50 newborn infants each, will be fed for 30 days an infant formula
      supplemented with either 4.9 mg/100 kcal or 10.6 mg/100 kcal of nucleotides or with no
      supplementation. Newborns will be monitored prospectively for the following outcome
      parameters:

        -  Growth percentiles.

        -  Behaviour and infantile colic.

        -  Bowel habits.

        -  Side effects.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
